        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "The Permian Basin is an area in Western Texas and Southeastern New Mexico covering more than 86,000 square miles. It accounts for 40% of the nation's oil and in 2020, was producing over 4 million barrels of oil a day. Environment Texas traveled the area speaking to residents and local experts to find out what it was like to live in the oil capital of Texas."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "tags": [
        {
          "tag": "Text",
          "category": "Transcript"
        }
      ],
      "uuid": "447fcb88-7f25-4e0a-883c-06e9c5ce520b"
    },
    {
      "start_time": 11,
      "end_time": 23,
      "annotation": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Lorraine Spickermann is an instructor with the School of Education the University of Texas - Permian Basin. She has lived in the Permian for more than 20 years and seen the impacts of the fossil fuel industry on students, residents and the environment. Here are some of her thoughts. "
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "tags": [
        {
          "tag": "Text",
          "category": "Transcript"
        }
      ],
      "uuid": "fbf0b7ef-71c6-451d-97f4-f8502439b6ce"
    },
    {
      "start_time": 23,
      "end_time": 37,
      "annotation": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "So, when we first lived here, for the first ten or fifteen years, we never experienced earthquakes. More recently, we do have very small ones: two and four, and they're centered north of town or north-east of town."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "tags": [
        {
          "tag": "Audio",
          "category": "Transcript"
        },
        {
          "tag": "Lorraine Spickermann",
          "category": "Interviewee"
        }
      ],
      "uuid": "1422c2b0-5e21-4540-ac41-fed535213bcc"
    },
    {
      "start_time": 37,
      "end_time": 41,
      "annotation": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Okay. What's north and north-east of town?"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "tags": [
        {
          "tag": "Audio",
          "category": "Transcript"
        },
        {
          "tag": "Micheal Lewis",
          "category": "Interviewer"
        }
      ],
      "uuid": "be78dc62-29d4-4088-99a9-c8e95e6dda74"
    },
    {
      "start_time": 41,
      "end_time": 45,
      "annotation": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Fields. Pumpjacks. "
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "tags": [
        {
          "tag": "Audio",
          "category": "Transcript"
        },
        {
          "tag": "Lorraine Spickermann",
          "category": "Interviewee"
        }
      ],
      "uuid": "c6434ea7-86ee-42bc-b36a-98884f83c67b"
    },
    {
      "start_time": 45,
      "end_time": 55,
      "annotation": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "So that's where the fracking and the the extraction is actually happening, right? And it just happens to coincide with where the earthquakes are centered?"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "tags": [
        {
          "tag": "Audio",
          "category": "Transcript"
        },
        {
          "tag": "Lorraine Spickermann",
          "category": "Interviewee"
        }
      ],
      "uuid": "235d999f-dddc-46ff-a1fc-5211761781ff"
    },
    {
      "start_time": 55,
      "end_time": 56,
      "annotation": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Potentially, yes. "
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "tags": [
        {
          "tag": "Audio",
          "category": "Transcript"
        },
        {
          "tag": "Lorraine Spickermann",
          "category": "Interviewee"
        }
