      "uuid": "72dec99b-183c-4722-a1ef-7db097c95229"
    },
    {
      "start_time": 59,
      "end_time": 76,
      "annotation": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "I had an exchange student visiting from China, and one day she said \"oh, I love the smell.\" That's an awful smell. Well, it's actually the smell of fuel, the burn off, just the smell of whatever you know we put into the chemicals to make it so you can identified. "
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "tags": [
        {
          "tag": "Audio",
          "category": "Transcript"
        },
        {
          "tag": "Lorraine Spickermann",
          "category": "Interviewee"
        }
      ],
      "uuid": "ef14ebfe-6121-4164-b835-578373676252"
    },
    {
      "start_time": 76,
      "end_time": 93,
      "annotation": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "To her that's a beautiful smell, and I'm thinking, that's an industrial pollutant smell. And other days we don't smell it, but sometimes you do smell the twang which way the wind's blowing. So to me that's something that I don't personally enjoy but for her she lives in an industrial town that's a normal smell."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
